<h2 id='authentication-activity'>Authentication Activity</h2>
<p>The following functions provide Inspetor with information on when a user logs in our out of an account within your product:</p>

<ul>
<li><a href="#account-login">trackLogin</a></li>
<li><a href="#account-logout">trackLogout</a></li>
</ul>

<p>All functions for tracking authentication activity require an <a href="#inspetorauth">InspetorAuth</a> object as an argument and return <code>true</code> upon successful execution. Otherwise, one of the following exceptions will be thrown:</p>

<table><thead>
<tr>
<th>Exception</th>
<th>Description</th>
</tr>
</thead><tbody>
<tr>
<td><strong><a href="#inspetorauthexception">AuthException</a></strong></td>
<td>The Auth object provided is invalid</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong><a href="#inspetorgeneralexception">generalException</a></strong></td>
<td>The timestamps passed as Auth object properties are invalid</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong><a href="#trackerexception">TrackerException</a></strong></td>
<td>An internal error occurred (<em>This should never happen</em>)</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>

<p><h3 id='account-login'>Account Login</h3><pre class="highlight php tab-php"><code><span class="cp">&lt;?php</span>

<span class="k">use</span> <span class="nx">Inspetor</span><span class="p">;</span>

<span class="nv">$inspetor</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="nv">$this</span><span class="o">-&gt;</span><span class="na">getConfiguredInspetor</span><span class="p">();</span>

<span class="nv">$inspetor</span><span class="o">-&gt;</span><span class="na">trackLogin</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nv">$auth</span><span class="p">);</span>

<span class="cp">?&gt;</span>
</code></pre><pre class="highlight python tab-python"><code><span class="kn">import</span> <span class="nn">inspetor</span>

<span class="n">inspetor</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="bp">self</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">getConfiguredInspetor</span><span class="p">()</span>

<span class="n">inspetor</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">track_login</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">auth</span><span class="p">)</span>

</code></pre>
<p>Send information to Inspetor on every login attempt</p>

<table><thead>
<tr>
<th>Argument</th>
<th>Type</th>
<th>Description</th>
</tr>
</thead><tbody>
<tr>
<td>auth</td>
<td>Inspetor/Model/<a href="#inspetorauth">InspetorAuth</a></td>
<td>The Auth object that describes the login</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</p>

<p><h3 id='account-logout'>Account Logout</h3><pre class="highlight php tab-php"><code><span class="cp">&lt;?php</span>

<span class="k">use</span> <span class="nx">Inspetor</span><span class="p">;</span>

<span class="nv">$inspetor</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="nv">$this</span><span class="o">-&gt;</span><span class="na">getConfiguredInspetor</span><span class="p">();</span>

<span class="nv">$inspetor</span><span class="o">-&gt;</span><span class="na">trackLogout</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nv">$auth</span><span class="p">);</span>

<span class="cp">?&gt;</span>
</code></pre><pre class="highlight python tab-python"><code><span class="kn">import</span> <span class="nn">inspetor</span>

<span class="n">inspetor</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="bp">self</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">getConfiguredInspetor</span><span class="p">()</span>

<span class="n">inspetor</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">track_logout</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">auth</span><span class="p">)</span>

</code></pre>
<p>Send information to Inspetor every time an account (<em>e.g. user</em>) logs out.</p>

<table><thead>
<tr>
<th>Argument</th>
<th>Type</th>
<th>Description</th>
</tr>
</thead><tbody>
<tr>
<td>auth</td>
<td>Inspetor/Model/<a href="#inspetorauth">InspetorAuth</a></td>
<td>The Auth object that describes the logout</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</p>
